Remarks . Although we did not examine specimens of
Parahelice pilimana
from its type locality ( New Caledonia ) or the adjacent area, the Taiwanese specimens agree well with the descriptions in A. Milne-Edwards (1873) and
Sakai et al . (2006)
, including carapace ( Fig. 4A ;
Sakai et al . 2006
: figs. 82, 83), male chelae ( Fig. 4B; A . Milne- Edwards 1873: pl. 18(1a);
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 82), male infraorbital ridges ( Fig. 4C ;
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 65), and G1s ( Fig. 4 E–H;
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 71).
